EXPLAIN  SELECT i, j, MIN(i+j) OVER (ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING) min FROM t ORDER BY NULL DESC;
Query Plan
========================================
|ID|OPERATOR       |NAME|EST. ROWS|COST|
----------------------------------------
|0 |WINDOW FUNCTION|    |4        |38  |
|1 | TABLE SCAN    |t   |4        |37  |
========================================

Outputs & filters: 
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([t.i], [t.j], [T_FUN_MIN(t.i + t.j)]), filter(nil), 
      win_expr(T_FUN_MIN(t.i + t.j)), partition_by(nil), order_by(nil), window_type(RANGE), upper(UNBOUNDED PRECEDING), lower(UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING)
  1 - output([t.i], [t.j], [t.i + t.j]), filter(nil), 
      access([t.i], [t.j]), partitions(p0)

